264
00:25:44,571 --> 00:25:47,574
He created the android unit
at NorthAm Robotics.

265
00:25:47,657 --> 00:25:50,827
He's responsible for
the technology that allows you
to mimic human expression.

266
00:25:50,869 --> 00:25:55,707
- What happened to him?
- Well, NorthAm laid him off
when they shut down the unit,

267
00:25:55,749 --> 00:25:58,626
so he started this place,
and I took over when he died.

268
00:25:58,710 --> 00:26:02,839
- I'm sorry to hear that.
- He would have been
absolutely thrilled to meet you.

269
00:26:02,922 --> 00:26:05,175
I-l-I'm Rupert Burns.

270
00:26:05,258 --> 00:26:07,802
- It's a real honor.
- The honor is mine.

271
00:26:07,886 --> 00:26:12,182
- Hey! You and l- we're the same!

272
00:26:14,017 --> 00:26:16,394
- Let's get loco, robo!

273
00:26:16,478 --> 00:26:18,354
Whoo-hoo!

274
00:26:18,438 --> 00:26:21,816
- Shut her off or I will.
- Oh.

275
00:26:23,860 --> 00:26:25,570
Okay.

276
00:26:28,698 --> 00:26:30,658
Thank you.

277
00:26:31,993 --> 00:26:34,746
Is this your father's work?

278
00:26:34,829 --> 00:26:39,250
Yeah- Well, it's-
it's our work, you could say.

279
00:26:39,292 --> 00:26:42,921
I haven't really been able
to restrain myself from continuing...

280
00:26:42,962 --> 00:26:47,092
to tinker with the relentlessly
unfashionable android technology.

281
00:26:47,133 --> 00:26:51,304
As a matter of fact,
I've actually gotten to a point...

282
00:26:51,387 --> 00:26:55,391
