- Thank you.

285
00:27:10,073 --> 00:27:12,575
- Amazing!
- Yeah.

286
00:27:12,617 --> 00:27:18,081
Unfortunately, nobody seems terribly
interested in funding my research.

287
00:27:18,164 --> 00:27:21,543
- But-
- I am.

288
00:27:22,794 --> 00:27:25,004
I will fund your research.

289
00:27:26,256 --> 00:27:29,175
Yeah?

290
00:27:29,217 --> 00:27:31,761
That'd be cool.

291
00:27:37,100 --> 00:27:41,604
Thank you, darlin'. Okay.
Andrew, I want to make it
very clear:

292
00:27:41,688 --> 00:27:45,900
This is an external physical
upgrade only in the strictest
sense of the word.

293
00:27:45,984 --> 00:27:49,154
You'll feel nothing.
None of your internal mechanisms
will be changed.

294
00:27:49,237 --> 00:27:51,781
You'll still be subject
to the parameters
of your positronic brain.

295
00:27:51,865 --> 00:27:53,908
- Is that clear?
- Understood.

296
00:27:53,992 --> 00:27:56,244
Okay, good. Now,

297
00:27:56,286 --> 00:28:02,000
have you given any thought
whatsoever as to what age
you'd like to be?

298
00:28:02,083 --> 00:28:04,836
Officially,
I am 62 years old.

299
00:28:06,588 --> 00:28:08,840
- Let's take off 25 years.
What do ya say?
- Fifteen.

300
00:28:08,923 --> 00:28:10,884
- Twenty. Good.
- Perfect.

301
00:28:14,179 --> 00:28:17,682
Now, Andrew, believe it or not,
the secret to all this is actually...

302
00:28:17,766 --> 00:28:19,893
- imperfection.
- Imperfection?

303
00:28:19,976 --> 00:28:22,395
Yeah. Things like...

304
00:28:22,437 --> 00:28:26,232
wrinkles, uh,
less-than-perfect teeth,

305
00:28:26,274 --> 00:28:28,735
details like fading scars,
little pockmark-

306
00:28:28,818 --> 00:28:31,571
Look at my nose.
See my nose?

307
00:28:31,654 --> 00:28:34,199
- It's bulbous and slightly irregular?
- It is.

308
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:37,744
Well, I'm the only one
who's got my nose,
and that's what makes me, me.

309
00:28:37,827 --> 00:28:40,580
We need to incorporate
these features into your design...

310
00:28:40,663 --> 00:28:43,166
so that you can be
the only one of you.

311
00:28:43,208 --> 00:28:46,669
That's what makes us unique,
is those imperfections.

312
00:28:46,753 --> 00:28:49,214
I see.
Like the shape of your head.

313
00:28:51,508 --> 00:28:54,677
- What about the shape of my head?
- It's huge.

314
00:28:56,012 --> 00:28:58,556
Oh.

315
00:29:00,141 --> 00:29:03,061
But lovely.

316
00:29:03,144 --> 00:29:05,396
Thank you.

317
00:29:14,072 --> 00:29:15,990
Oh.

318
00:29:18,284 --> 00:29:20,203
Ah. Oh.

319
00:29:26,668 --> 00:29:30,338
- What happened? What's going on?

320
00:29:31,423 --> 00:29:34,217
What happened?

321
00:29:34,300 --> 00:29:36,636
I saw the inner me.

322
00:30:26,227 --> 00:30:29,230
- Is it ready?
- Okay.

323
00:30:34,986 --> 00:30:37,322
Please, be careful.
Don't drop me.

324
00:30:37,363 --> 00:30:39,324
- I'm being careful. Oh, my God!

325
00:30:39,365 --> 00:30:41,993
Just relax,
relax, relax.

326
00:30:42,035 --> 00:30:44,329
Why did you do that?
That wasn't very funny.

327
00:30:44,412 --> 00:30:46,498
Just keepin' ya
on your toes.

328
00:30:46,581 --> 00:30:49,501
- I don't have any toes.
- You do now.

329
00:30:51,503 --> 00:30:54,964
I do.
And hands.

330
00:30:55,048 --> 00:30:57,717
And fingers.
How do I look?

331
00:30:57,801 --> 00:30:59,969
See for yourself.

332
00:31:32,544 --> 00:31:34,462
Thank you.

333
00:32:07,203 --> 00:32:10,457
- Beautiful.

334
00:32:10,540 --> 00:32:13,376
-Sorry.
