- He's had an upgrade.

348
00:32:51,039 --> 00:32:53,875
- I know that.

349
00:32:53,958 --> 00:32:56,753
- Oh!
- Hello.

350
00:32:56,836 --> 00:33:00,757
Hello! It is you.

351
00:33:04,677 --> 00:33:06,763
- You know him?
- Yes.

352
00:33:06,846 --> 00:33:08,264
- You know me?
- Yes.

353
00:33:08,348 --> 00:33:10,308
- Who are you? No?
- I'm Little Miss. Yes.

354
00:33:10,391 --> 00:33:12,560
- That's Little Miss.
- No.

355
00:33:12,602 --> 00:33:14,229
- No? No?
- No.

356
00:33:14,312 --> 00:33:17,565
- No, that's Portia.
- Portia? Yes.

357
00:33:17,607 --> 00:33:19,567
- Portia?
- Yes.

358
00:33:20,860 --> 00:33:23,363
- Who's Portia?
- My granddaughter.

359
00:33:23,446 --> 00:33:26,116
- Your granddaughter?
- Yes. Yes.

360
00:33:26,199 --> 00:33:28,118
- Is this some kind of trick?
- No.

361
00:33:28,201 --> 00:33:30,745
- You're Little Miss?
- Yes.

362
00:33:30,829 --> 00:33:33,331
Why do you have to look
like her?

363
00:33:33,373 --> 00:33:37,419
- There is and can be
only one Little Miss.
- Really?

364
00:33:37,502 --> 00:33:41,172
- Yes!
- It's a genetic resemblance.
Sometimes it skips a generation.

365
00:33:41,214 --> 00:33:44,217
- I don't care. I don't like it.
- I can see that.

366
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:47,262
But if you took a moment,
which I see you're not
inclined to do right now,

367
00:33:47,345 --> 00:33:50,640
you'd realize Portia and I
are very different people.

368
00:33:52,809 --> 00:33:55,687
- Why is she imitating you?

369
00:33:55,728 --> 00:33:58,273
- What's so funny?
- You are.

370
00:33:58,356 --> 00:34:00,733
I'm not trying
to be funny.

371
00:34:00,817 --> 00:34:04,070
Things have certainly
changed around here.

372
00:34:05,155 --> 00:34:08,116
That happens
after 20 years.

373
00:34:09,868 --> 00:34:13,663
I have so much to tell you.
Come. Come with me.

374
00:34:16,583 --> 00:34:18,877
It is you.

375
00:34:18,960 --> 00:34:21,087
Yes.

376
00:34:21,129 --> 00:34:23,131
Portia.

377
00:34:26,634 --> 00:34:29,053
- Hello, my friend.
- Hello, Little Miss.

378
00:34:31,306 --> 00:34:33,266
Whose daughter is she?

379
00:34:33,308 --> 00:34:35,977
- Lloyd's.
- Oh. Now the rudeness makes sense.

380
00:34:57,415 --> 00:35:00,543
Go.
Go home to your master.

381
00:35:02,587 --> 00:35:05,048
You don't have a home,
do you?

382
00:35:07,300 --> 00:35:09,719
I don't have food.
I don't eat.

383
00:35:14,933 --> 00:35:17,852
Come in. We'll keep
each other company.

384
00:35:42,252 --> 00:35:47,298
I know you don't like me.
Well, I don't like you either.
I just wanna make that clear.

385
00:35:47,382 --> 00:35:50,510
- It couldn't be more clear
if you spat in my face.
- I can't.

386
00:35:50,593 --> 00:35:53,430
I don't have
a mucous gland.

387
00:36:02,313 --> 00:36:05,233
Would it be possible to have
a slightly longer conversation?

388
00:36:10,738 --> 00:36:13,158
May my canine companion
enter also?

389
00:36:17,495 --> 00:36:19,414
Thank you.

390
00:36:33,636 --> 00:36:36,014
Is this your sculpture?

391
00:36:37,557 --> 00:36:41,352
No, I'm restoring it.
I'm a preservation architect.

392
00:36:41,436 --> 00:36:43,646
It's quite horrendous.

393
00:36:44,856 --> 00:36:47,192
How ugly was it
before you restored it?

394
00:36:47,275 --> 00:36:52,280
- Listen. First, you get mad
at me because of how I look.
- Mm-hmm.

395
00:36:52,322 --> 00:36:56,534
Tonight you show up at my door,
announce that you don't like me,
and then you criticize my work.

396
00:36:56,618 --> 00:36:59,704
Once again, I apologize
for telling the truth.

397
00:36:59,788 --> 00:37:04,042
But it can't be helped.
It's my programming.

398
00:37:04,125 --> 00:37:06,878
What is it exactly
that you want?

399
00:37:06,961 --> 00:37:10,298
Family.

400
00:37:10,340 --> 00:37:12,300
My last name is Martin,

401
00:37:12,342 --> 00:37:15,345
I am so named because
your great-grandfather
and grandmother...

402
00:37:15,428 --> 00:37:18,264
considered me to be
a member of your family.

403
00:37:18,306 --> 00:37:22,185
Now, Sir is dead.
Little Miss is getting older.

404
00:37:22,268 --> 00:37:25,188
You don't like me, but at least
you'll talk to me if I knock
on your door long enough.

405
00:37:25,271 --> 00:37:27,732
- Is that a joke?
- No.

406
00:37:27,774 --> 00:37:30,860
Would you like to hear a joke?
This Buddhist walks up
to a hot dog vendor and says,

407
00:37:30,944 --> 00:37:32,862
" Make me one
with everything."

408
00:37:37,242 --> 00:37:41,454
- Andrew, do you- do you have
any friends at all?
- No.

409
00:37:41,538 --> 00:37:47,001
Only Woofy, who's very sweet,
but not very challenging
on a conversational level.

410
00:37:47,085 --> 00:37:50,213
That is the extent
of his skills.

411
00:37:50,296 --> 00:37:53,466
- So you want someone
to talk to?
- With.

412
00:37:53,550 --> 00:37:57,470
- Even if that person doesn't like you?
- You can't have everything.

413
00:37:57,554 --> 00:38:02,142
Is that right? Is it,
"You can have everything"?
Seems like some people do,

414
00:38:02,225 --> 00:38:04,644
so I'm somewhat confused
on that level.

415
00:38:08,398 --> 00:38:11,109
- Sit down. Let's talk.
- Thank you.

416
00:38:11,192 --> 00:38:13,111
Mm-hmm.

417
00:38:18,908 --> 00:38:23,538
Hey there, handsome. Andrew,
could I get you anything to drink?

418
00:38:23,621 --> 00:38:28,126
- Sorry, I have no stomach.
- Oh. Could I get something for him?

419
00:38:28,168 --> 00:38:31,421
- He has a stomach. Yes.
- Do you think he's hungry?

420
00:39:13,004 --> 00:39:16,341
- How is she?
- She's sleeping.

421
00:39:16,424 --> 00:39:18,343
What happened?

422
00:39:18,426 --> 00:39:21,054
She had a stroke.

423
00:39:53,336 --> 00:39:58,091
Mm. There you are.

424
00:39:59,592 --> 00:40:02,011
Little Miss.

425
00:40:19,612 --> 00:40:21,531
Hmm.

426
00:40:54,397 --> 00:40:56,733
She's gone?

427
00:41:09,871 --> 00:41:12,999
It's cruel that you can cry
and I cannot.

428
00:41:13,041 --> 00:41:18,254
